The paper discusses bibliometric indicators for assessing individual scientists, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and dissemination of digital information, including bibliometric data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the retrieval of information from large collections, including bibliographic databases. cs.CY (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they also involve the analysis of large datasets. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility as it deals with the analysis of networks, which can include citation networks.
